    "html" :
    
    
    "Electrolyte reacts with alkalis and water and generates a considerable amount of heat. Electrolyte destroys paper, wood and textiles and has a corrosive reaction to metals. Electrolyte is a fluid that is hazardous to water and causes ecological damage as a result of pH changes."
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
